  + [purpose] is compare finite landmark displacement across sparse resonance, dense Lambda heat, and contribution-layer offset extrema
  + [not_purpose] is new scans, denser offset grids, proof, disproof, RH evidence, zero certification, critical-line authority, primary zero detection, or identity fusion
  + [proof_status] is finite_cross_layer_landmark_displacement_not_rh_evidence

& [MeasuredComparison] is existing_trace_displacement_synthesis
  + [reference_labels] are first_zero_ordinate_reference, second_zero_ordinate_reference, and third_zero_ordinate_reference as labels only
  + [sparse_layer] is vertical_resonance candidate rows from existing trace
  + [dense_layer] is Lambda window/cutoff candidate rows from existing trace
  + [contribution_layer] is Lambda phasor reference contribution offset rows from existing trace
  + [displacement_measure] is signed sampled_t - reference_t when available and absolute distance to nearest reference label otherwise
  + [comparison_policy] is compare per layer and per metric before drawing any cross-layer inference
  + [allowed_output] is analysis pass and focal-point update only

  = must: use existing trace rows only
  = must: preserve sparse resonance and dense Lambda heat as separate layers
  = must: preserve contribution-layer offset maxima/minima as coarse three-point stencil behavior only
  = must: report nearest distances and directional offsets without zero certification
  = must: decide whether cross-window/cutoff stability class is justified or whether overlay displacement should pause
  = must: preserve proof_status finite_cross_layer_landmark_displacement_not_rh_evidence
  - never: collapse sparse, dense, and contribution layers into one RH identity
  - never: authorize denser scans from displacement alone

& [CrossLayerLandmarkDisplacementSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and synthesis_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_bounded_cross_layer_displacement_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is the existing traces contain enough nearest-reference and offset-local structure to compare layer displacement without adding a new grid

(cross_layer_landmark_displacement) :finite cross-layer displacement synthesis: /reference labels, sparse resonance, dense Lambda heat, contribution offsets/ |RH evidence|
